{
  "texts": [
    "This creates a 3D data cube or hypercube with two spatial dimensions and one spectral dimension that supports detailed analysis of both spatial and spectral characteristics within a sample.",
    "Each material exhibits a distinctive spectral signature, characterized by specific patterns of light absorption, reflection, transmission across different wavelengths (Sarić et al. 2022).",
    "These spectral signatures enable the identification and differentiation of materials within each pixel of an image.",
    "HSI operates in reflection, transmission, and fluorescence modes, using four main image acquisition methods: point scanning (whiskbroom), line scanning (pushbroom), area scanning (tunable filter), and snapshot imaging.",
    "Point scanning captures one pixel at a time and moves across the sample, line scanning captures a line of pixels, area scanning records the entire sample one wavelength at a time, and snapshot imaging captures the entire hypercube in a single shot."
  ]
}